This:
- Extracts day and month from K.
- Checks the two‑digit year (`MID(K,7,2)`). If it is `"22"` we output `"2022"`; otherwise we use the current full year.
- Keeps the time part unchanged.

We applied this formula to every data row (rows 2 through max_row) in column C, saved the workbook to the output directory, recalculated formulas, and verified a few sample results (including a row where K’s year is `"22"`). The results match the required format.

